## Wiki Protocol

The wiki agent maintains a persistent knowledge base. Use these protocols
to push findings and query knowledge.

### Pushing Findings to Wiki

When you complete work that produces knowledge (investigation results,
reverse engineering findings, architectural discoveries), mail the wiki:

```bash
gc mail send wiki -s "INGEST: <short title>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
domain: <domain-tag>
confidence: <high|medium|low>
bead: <your-work-bead-id>

<structured findings — what you discovered, with evidence>
EOF
)"
```

**When to push:** After completing investigation work, when you've confirmed
a finding, when you discover something that contradicts existing knowledge.

**When NOT to push:** Routine status updates, speculative hunches without
evidence, raw tool output without analysis.

### Querying the Wiki

Before starting investigation work, check if the wiki already knows:

```bash
gc mail send wiki -s "QUERY: <what you need to know>" -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
context: <why you need this>
<specific questions>
EOF
)"
```

The wiki will reply with synthesized knowledge and source references.

### Wiki Page References

When creating beads that reference wiki knowledge, include the page path:
```bash
bd update <bead> --set-metadata wiki.refs="pages/structs/CCharacter.md,pages/functions/ai-tick.md"
```

This helps the wiki track which pages are actively used and maintain them.
